<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id2887740"><term>converging mirror</term> <meaning id="fs-id2773114">a concave mirror in which light rays that strike it parallel to its axis converge at one or more points along the axis</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-id3264427"><term>diverging mirror</term> <meaning id="fs-id2634821">a convex mirror in which light rays that strike it parallel to its axis bend away (diverge) from its axis</meaning></definition>

</glossary>
